Typically, there’s big two week demo before the election. Art installations, improvisations, games and performances.

Last weekend, the press tried to attend the demonstration in Rabat. Salut!

The following is a graphic of the thought process of a hypothetical dancer:

1) Would this piece be interesting in x

2) Would this piece be fun to improvise

3) Can I take on this workload given the available time frame, and do I care about it?

4) What are the varied demographics of the audience, and is sustainability possible given them? What is my goal re: audience experience?

5) Is it crazy to think of moving to Morocco?

It’s so good to be able to improvise, with a group. So much of the time, it’s me and my router.

“I was just going to front flip off the building, but instead I’m getting a certificate for reading books.”

I think this is Satwinder Bains and Jeremy Stewart. Are you talking about the Push Festival? Because it is so worth it and something that I have great memories of doing. I feel like a beginner without that community. I should do something about that! ..You could guest teach some improv if you ever get the chance.
